Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.88,0:54:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as sin,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.88,0:54:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sackcloth,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.88,0:54:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,ashes,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.07,0:54:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,penance.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.36,0:54:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.36,0:54:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of a
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.36,0:54:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,dismal
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.36,0:54:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,downness
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.36,0:54:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to it
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.36,0:54:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.36,0:54:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.36,0:54:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And here
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.36,0:54:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.36,0:54:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.36,0:54:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.36,0:54:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,how it
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.36,0:54:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.36,0:54:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,through the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.36,0:54:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,animal kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.36,0:54:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,over periods
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.36,0:54:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.36,0:54:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So that we
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.36,0:54:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,re-contextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.69,0:54:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.07,0:54:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,not as
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.07,0:54:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,sin and
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.07,0:54:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,evil
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.28,0:54:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,requiring
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.28,0:54:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,penance,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.28,0:54:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,guilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.28,0:54:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,self-hatred,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.28,0:54:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and even
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.28,0:54:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,self-destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.55,0:54:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,out of guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.55,0:54:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,On the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.96,0:54:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,contrary,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.96,0:54:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it's
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.96,0:54:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,our
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.96,0:54:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.03,0:54:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.03,0:54:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.03,0:54:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,think about
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.03,0:54:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.05,0:54:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,locus
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.05,0:54:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.05,0:54:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.05,0:54:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.05,0:54:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,call all
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.09,0:54:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,these people
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.09,0:55:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,evil here,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.09,0:55:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.09,0:55:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.59,0:55:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,call all
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.59,0:55:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,these people
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.59,0:55:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.59,0:55:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,just because
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.59,0:55:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,they calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.59,0:55:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.59,0:55:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.59,0:55:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.59,0:55:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,hippopotamuses
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.59,0:55:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,can be
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.59,0:55:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,quite kindly.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.59,0:55:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There was
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.80,0:55:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a wonderful
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.80,0:55:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,one on
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.80,0:55:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the History
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.80,0:55:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is nursing the alligators.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.42,0:55:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's put in a good word for the hippopotamus.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.63,0:55:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bad-looking thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.94,0:55:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They need somebody to speak for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.28,0:55:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.84,0:55:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we can take the kinesiologic test
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.67,0:55:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and go through the entire intellectual history of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.13,0:55:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We can go all the way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.19,0:55:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the greatest time was the Golden Era in Greece,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.90,0:55:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and life has really gone downhill since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.53,0:55:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Life was at its peak in Athens, in Greece,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.46,0:56:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in about 350, 400, 500 B.C.,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.30,0:56:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the time of Socrates, Plato, Aristotle, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.51,0:56:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we can go through the great books of the Western world
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.11,0:56:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrate what is the intellectual background
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.86,0:56:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of understanding of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.69,0:56:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the basis of all of the Western world,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.26,0:56:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and we calibrate all the great names in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.19,0:56:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All the great names in history,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.96,0:56:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.09,0:56:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And this in itself serves as quite an interesting thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.03,0:56:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They say it would take 10 years to study the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.90,0:56:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Take 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.90,0:56:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Takes 10 years, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.28,0:56:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.34,0:56:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We notice the limitation of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.44,0:56:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We notice that Freud, Einstein,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.28,0:56:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.55,0:56:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,499.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.67,0:56:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the 400s...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.07,0:56:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the world of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.07,0:57:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the world of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.07,0:57:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Kant, Kepler, the great astronomers.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.15,0:57:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The great names in history here are all in the mid-400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.15,0:57:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hippocrates at 485,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.15,0:57:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the discovery of the human...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.15,0:57:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Galen...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.15,0:57:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Isaac Newton, 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.15,0:57:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,499 is about as high as you can get with the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.23,0:57:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And at 499, you have to leave the world of cause and effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.23,0:57:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm of reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.23,0:57:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because 500 is the emergence of the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.23,0:57:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 500 is the world of the linear,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.51,0:57:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,which is provable, documentable, and provable.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.51,0:57:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,From 500 and up, suddenly reality jumps to the subjective,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.51,0:57:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,experiential, not provable, not logical,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.51,0:57:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be documented, but transformative.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.51,0:57:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, from 500 and up, our spiritual energies,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.51,0:58:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore, people ask me,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.67,0:58:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the relationship between science and spirituality,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.67,0:58:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,or science and theology?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.67,0:58:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And I tell them, there isn't any.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.67,0:58:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't any.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.98,0:58:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Two different realms altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.98,0:58:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The 400s can talk about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.98,0:58:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,can talk about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.98,0:58:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's all they can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.98,0:58:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's intellectualization.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.98,0:58:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't prove the existence of God through the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.23,0:58:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I was once a rabid atheist,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.23,0:58:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and I remember St. Thomas Aquinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.23,0:58:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I had straight A in theology and everything and such,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.23,0:58:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,even though I was an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.48,0:58:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Thomas Aquinas says,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.48,0:58:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,arguments, which he derived from Aristotle,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.48,0:58:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,arguments for the proof of the existence of God
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.48,0:58:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,are considered nonsense,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.13,0:58:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,especially the argument for first cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.19,0:58:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is infinite has no beginning or ending,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.19,0:59:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so how could it have a cause?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.19,0:59:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The argument for first cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.19,0:59:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Friday afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.19,0:59:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we go to the bar and, of course, argue about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.15,0:59:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it was fun being an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.15,0:59:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a rabid atheist for some years.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.15,0:59:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already told you how I arrived there.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.57,0:59:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Isaac Newton then is 499, Plato 485.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.57,0:59:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,See the great names throughout history,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.57,0:59:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Shakespeare, Spinoza.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.53,0:59:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And we always point out that, unfortunately,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.53,0:59:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Marx got in, inadvertently put in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.53,0:59:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because of his historical importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.53,0:59:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But at 130, he brings this whole scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.53,0:59:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all of them collectively,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.53,0:59:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with Marx, comes to 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.63,0:59:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Without Marx, it comes to 465.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.63,0:59:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, falsehood has a serious,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.63,0:59:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,deleterious effect on society,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.63,0:59:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and history of Marxism merely demonstrates that fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.63,0:59:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fallacy there was a projecting
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.63,0:59:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,duality of perpetrator-victim into the world
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.63,1:00:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and politicizing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.63,1:00:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so move to the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.63,1:00:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move to the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.26,1:00:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the world, the linear, provable world,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.67,1:00:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which is content, content.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.67,1:00:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But the content occurs in an approximate field,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.67,1:00:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and that even in a greater context,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.67,1:00:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the nonlinear context, the infinite context,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.67,1:00:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the absolute by which we calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.73,1:00:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth of anything here is in contrast to this.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.73,1:00:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The approximate field is local conditions.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.73,1:00:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Things appear when local conditions,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.59,1:00:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,when potentiality becomes an actuality,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.59,1:00:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,when local conditions are favorable.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.01,1:00:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So the local conditions don't cause it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.01,1:00:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They allow the potentiality to actualize.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.07,1:01:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The seed, when it gets sun and warmth and water,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.07,1:01:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,its potential becomes an actual.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.21,1:01:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But the sun and the water does not cause it to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.28,1:01:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So in appropriate circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.28,1:01:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,this is called in logic, in ethics itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.28,1:01:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,situational ethics,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.28,1:01:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,which some religions don't like
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.53,1:01:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because they think it can be used as a cop-out excuse.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.53,1:01:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But the law recognizes that the degree of guilt, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.53,1:01:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on the conditions at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.63,1:01:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And insanity, defense, all these things take that into account.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.63,1:01:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, from our own research,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.69,1:01:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we come to the discovery
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.69,1:01:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that even without culpability,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.17,1:01:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you are still responsible and accountable.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.17,1:01:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The act, you are still accountable and responsible karmically,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.09,1:01:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,even though you may have very little culpability
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.19,1:01:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,due to other factors.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.19,1:02:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to differentiate between culpability
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.19,1:02:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and accountability and responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.34,1:02:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.82,1:02:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.65,1:02:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That which attracts, this is called lower mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.65,1:02:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is less evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.65,1:02:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's less evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.65,1:02:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That mind, for instance, cannot really comprehend kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.28,1:02:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness 160 is unable to comprehend it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.28,1:02:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.28,1:02:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it projects its own limitation onto what's out there
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.28,1:02:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and thinks it sees it as out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.28,1:02:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, it doesn't work unless the people involved
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.28,1:02:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,reach consciousness level 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.36,1:02:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,200.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.36,1:02:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.36,1:02:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because otherwise it's dominated by lower mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.36,1:02:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which hangs out around 155,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.36,1:02:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the level of skepticism and all that, about 160.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.48,1:03:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unable to comprehend.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.48,1:03:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to move over 200 towards higher mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.48,1:03:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Higher mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.73,1:03:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have the capacity for faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.00,1:03:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the integrity with which a thing is spoken,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.00,1:03:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.00,1:03:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to sense it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.00,1:03:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can sense the integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.00,1:03:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't prove it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.09,1:03:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.09,1:03:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning it's a person that has no particular personal gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.09,1:03:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't make any difference whether it goes this way or that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.40,1:03:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That level of consciousness is called neutral.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.44,1:03:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,With neutral, if you get this job,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.44,1:03:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't get this job, you'll get another.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.44,1:03:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the big deal?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.44,1:03:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.82,1:03:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Easygoing.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.34,1:03:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,These people are very positionalized and emotionalized, everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.34,1:03:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionalized.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.34,1:03:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday's paper, the Arizona Republic,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.34,1:03:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,said in an article that people voted for a certain proposition
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.34,1:04:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,primarily with their emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.34,1:04:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's scary, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.11,1:04:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because they reason what's best for the country,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.11,1:04:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what's fair, what's equitable,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.11,1:04:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,just from emotion.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.11,1:04:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Just emotion.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.11,1:04:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.11,1:04:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So 155 is emotionalism without thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.11,1:04:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean sensitivity, et cetera, or balance.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.11,1:04:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So move to the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.80,1:04:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just to show, again,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.80,1:04:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we're trying to show a bridge between the Newtonian linear limitation
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.80,1:04:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and the nonlinear, which is the spiritual domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.80,1:04:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantum mechanics is, again, only a pedagogical technique.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.80,1:04:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't prove anything that we're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.80,1:04:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But it does provide a means of comprehending
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.80,1:04:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,why prayer is a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.80,1:04:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's effective.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.80,1:04:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This has to do with wave and particle and potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.82,1:05:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that potentiality becomes an actuality
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.88,1:05:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,under the appropriate conditions.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.88,1:05:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What's one of the conditions?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.88,1:05:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.88,1:05:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention is the Heisenberg process is intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.53,1:05:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So a man sits with his feet on the desk,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.76,1:05:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,imagines building the biggest, tallest building in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.11,1:05:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it gathers energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.11,1:05:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he gets his banker friends behind it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.11,1:05:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He talks to architects.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.11,1:05:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And in exactly one year, one year,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.36,1:05:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the Empire State Building went up on, what is it,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.36,1:05:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,32nd Street or 32nd Street?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.36,1:05:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,One year. One year.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.36,1:05:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Due to this, Native American steel workers,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.51,1:05:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,who were absolutely fearless of height,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.51,1:05:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,60 stories up walking on a beam.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.51,1:05:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, they were fearless.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.51,1:05:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see, it took the intention to make it happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.51,1:05:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's Wayne Dyer's very popular book,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.51,1:05:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Power of Intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.51,1:06:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention is what drives also all spiritual evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.51,1:06:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Your intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.55,1:06:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.07,1:06:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is explained extremely well.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.07,1:06:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is, let's say it's an analogy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.07,1:06:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not an explanation, not an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.07,1:06:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an analogy that by intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.59,1:06:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality becomes an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.59,1:06:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That is, the intention is part of the outer field,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.07,1:06:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is part of the field of context.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.07,1:06:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.07,1:06:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just, you get two different paradigms.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.57,1:06:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The proof, this is the world of provability.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.57,1:06:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is confirmable but not provable.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.57,1:06:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't prove you love somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.57,1:06:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't prove that you care about your dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.57,1:06:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No way to prove that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.55,1:07:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, this is limited and this is unlimited.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.63,1:07:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When you, in context,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.48,1:07:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in contemplation and meditation,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.48,1:07:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you try to move from this paradigm to this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.48,1:07:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to move from the specific linear restricted focused
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.75,1:07:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to the nonlinear overall context,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.75,1:07:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the overall context.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.78,1:07:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we'll move over to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.76,1:07:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Linear gradations.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.76,1:07:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we said the mind thinks dualistically,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.65,1:07:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,good and bad,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.30,1:07:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,black and white,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.30,1:07:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,high and low,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.30,1:07:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,hot and cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.30,1:07:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are positionalities.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.30,1:07:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because people say,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.30,1:07:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you mean a positionality?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.30,1:07:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Positionality is an optional point of view.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.30,1:07:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't exist in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.30,1:07:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't exist in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.55,1:07:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.55,1:07:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So I say,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.55,1:07:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,now, imagine three points here,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.88,1:08:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a point here,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.88,1:08:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a point here,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.88,1:08:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a point here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.88,1:08:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, now connect the dots.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.00,1:08:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You just made a triangle.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.00,1:08:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does the triangle exist?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.92,1:08:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.92,1:08:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Constellations of astrology are from the viewpoint of the witness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.56,1:08:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take a spaceship and go up there,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.56,1:08:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,there ain't no Sagittarius up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.56,1:08:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It only looks like Sagittarius from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.56,1:08:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,From here, it looks like a dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.65,1:08:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, they have no independent existence
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.65,1:08:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,except as a mentalization which you project into the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.78,1:08:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no constellation there.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.78,1:08:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.78,1:08:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.78,1:08:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody don't get it?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.94,1:08:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You can take any bunch of dots,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.77,1:08:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and as a kid,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.77,1:08:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you can make it into a horse or a dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.77,1:08:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's a projection.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.88,1:08:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.88,1:08:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And the crux of what we teach has to do,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.13,1:08:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.13,1:09:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with the differentiation between res interna,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.13,1:09:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,res cogitans,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.13,1:09:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and res externa,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.15,1:09:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the world the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.28,1:09:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A very important distinction.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.28,1:09:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Very important distinction.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.28,1:09:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Of Descartes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.28,1:09:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The ordinary mind thinks that
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.43,1:09:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,how it sees it is how it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.82,1:09:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That, of course, is the comment by Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.14,1:09:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That all men choose only what they perceive to be the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.14,1:09:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that they don't know the real good from the false good.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.14,1:09:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But that does reinforce your understanding of the innocence of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.31,1:09:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That mankind can only know what's within
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.39,1:09:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,without some kind of a higher teaching.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.39,1:09:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we use temperature.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.72,1:09:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We say this is very hot.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.72,1:09:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always say this is very cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.85,1:09:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That would...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.85,1:09:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one variable,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.85,1:09:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of heat or the absence of heat.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.85,1:09:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There aren't two variables, heat and cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.85,1:09:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.85,1:10:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Heat is either present or not present.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.85,1:10:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's present, we say it's hot.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.85,1:10:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's not present, we say it's cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.85,1:10:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,One variable, heat.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.85,1:10:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We do the same thing with the calibrated scale of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.85,1:10:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,One variable, called truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.85,1:10:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either present or not present, and to what degree.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.85,1:10:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Very simple, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.85,1:10:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrating the laws of consciousness is very, very simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.85,1:10:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The same with goodness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.27,1:10:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Light.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.27,1:10:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He said there's two opposites, light and darkness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.72,1:10:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There's either light or there's not light.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.15,1:10:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not two opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.15,1:10:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And the best example of all is on and off.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.35,1:10:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Offness is not the opposite of onness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.25,1:10:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't send offness down an electric wire.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.25,1:10:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Electricity is either present or not present.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.25,1:10:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Or it's not present.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.25,1:10:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't send offness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.25,1:10:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The opposite doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.25,1:10:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a meditation, you understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.25,1:10:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You only send electricity there or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.25,1:10:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Electricity is either there or it ain't there.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.25,1:11:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Heat is either there, light is either there.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.25,1:11:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And truth is either there or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.25,1:11:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So to what degree is truth there is the very purpose of calibrating levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.25,1:11:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be extremely there, very little there, hardly there at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.25,1:11:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,When you correlate that with all of human history and calibrate all the important figures, countries, books, movies, everything on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.27,1:11:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you come out with a configuration that even without kinesiology would make complete and total sense to anybody who's sane.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.27,1:11:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Move over.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.01,1:11:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.17,1:11:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual practices, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.17,1:11:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, for the first time really,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.00,1:11:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you can calibrate the relative truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.00,1:11:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the reality, the real authenticity of various things that are completely nonlinear and not provable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.00,1:12:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't prove that the Lord's Prayer, you know, does any good in the world at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.00,1:12:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you prove it?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.00,1:12:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't prove it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.00,1:12:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.03,1:12:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.03,1:12:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can certainly pick up the likelihood by calibrating it, calibrating it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.03,1:12:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lord's Prayer is 650.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.60,1:12:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, om, pronounced correctly as oh, calibrates different than ah-oh-um.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.02,1:12:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.02,1:12:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah-oh-um.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.11,1:12:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I say that because there's a translation by Satchitananda in which he does say A-U-M,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.40,1:12:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think it's incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.34,1:12:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite a bit of difference versus a three-syllable version of it, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.56,1:12:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting to notice.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.56,1:13:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Om Namah Shivaya.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.27,1:13:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all the great chants.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.85,1:13:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ammanipadmiham.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.59,1:13:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do an om for fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.68,1:13:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.11,1:13:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hold the people in the disaster, in the gopherry in mind and do om.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.93,1:13:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold them in mind and go om.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.10,1:13:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.10,1:13:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.76,1:13:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention is to bring them spiritual energy to uplift them, uplift them,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.76,1:13:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to pray to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.76,1:13:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,through periods of great stress
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.00,1:13:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.96,1:14:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,having been through periods of great stress myself
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.89,1:14:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only by surrendering to God
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.61,1:14:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that you survive them
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.64,1:14:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,as they take off your leg or your thumb
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.22,1:14:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever they do to you
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.31,1:14:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,surgery, no anesthesia, whatever
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.78,1:14:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of war you're about to blow up
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.93,1:14:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,all you can do is surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.88,1:14:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,continuously in a prayerful
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.07,1:14:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,attitude
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.61,1:14:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and surrender to God
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.69,1:14:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and once karmic proclivities will then
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.14,1:14:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,emerge of their own nature
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.68,1:14:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.13,1:14:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we know also from kinesiologic research
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.72,1:14:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's population
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.75,1:14:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,karma, population karma
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.48,1:14:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,whole populations
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.55,1:14:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we here in this room
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.05,1:14:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,are part of a population wave
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.86,1:14:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,population waves
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.93,1:14:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,each population seems to
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.11,1:14:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,be subject to various things
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.77,1:14:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,World War I, World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.47,1:14:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Crimean War, War of 1812
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.97,1:14:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,starvation, drought
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.14,1:14:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,okay let's ask about that
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.88,1:14:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that's just intuitive
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.39,1:15:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to ask this
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.68,1:15:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the highest good
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.42,1:15:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,there is such a thing as population karma
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.69,1:15:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,okay
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.77,1:15:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,intuition
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.43,1:15:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so a lot of things you intuit it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.84,1:15:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and it seems rather certain
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.22,1:15:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and actually you know it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.86,1:15:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,actually you know it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.75,1:15:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because you've existed over a great period of time
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.28,1:15:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and you know it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.94,1:15:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because you lived through it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.06,1:15:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,um
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.27,1:15:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,um
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.48,1:15:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,um
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.55,1:15:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,um
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.77,1:15:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,um
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.86,1:15:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,um
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.90,1:15:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,um
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.47,1:15:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,um
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.53,1:15:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,um
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.56,1:15:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,um
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.60,1:15:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,um
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.65,1:15:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so there is whole population
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.80,1:15:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic consequences
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.10,1:15:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,not consequences
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.23,1:15:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but opportunities
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.57,1:15:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's really
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.02,1:15:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,only when you're faced with the sword
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.57,1:15:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that you make that decision
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.03,1:15:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I surrender my life to thee oh lord
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.31,1:15:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,unreservedly
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.06,1:15:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,if you physically die
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.72,1:15:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you die
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.30,1:15:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.77,1:15:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you die you die
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.39,1:15:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,big deal
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.60,1:15:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember I told you the incident
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.89,1:15:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,here's this mind sitting here
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.27,1:16:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,with this horn sticking out of it
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.71,1:16:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it's about this far from the ship you know
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.53,1:16:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and this guy looks at me
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.34,1:16:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I said
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.02,1:16:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you go you go
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.26,1:16:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.35,1:16:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but you see how when you communicate that
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.30,1:16:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.11,1:16:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,how it reinforces the other person
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.56,1:16:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because the fear left his eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.35,1:16:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,he looked at me and he got that
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.02,1:16:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and he just
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.85,1:16:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,went that way too
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.84,1:16:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,as tough as it is
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.94,1:16:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,other than surrendering each step of the way
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.21,1:16:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,there isn't any other way
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.01,1:16:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and you look at me and you say
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.48,1:16:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you learned what you can from it
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.48,1:16:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and as I said
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.32,1:16:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,there is interestingly the survivors that we see
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.60,1:16:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in storm stories almost all mention how they prayed to God
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.39,1:16:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and the one that's most interesting
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.61,1:16:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple of people who got picked up
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.92,1:16:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in a tornado
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.43,1:16:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and lifted
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.65,1:16:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,like a block up in the air
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.02,1:16:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,there they are suspended a block up in the air
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.48,1:17:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,hundreds of feet up in the air
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.05,1:17:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in a state of profound peace over Canaan
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.23,1:17:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,several of them in a row I said
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.72,1:17:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it was like an infinite
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.93,1:17:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was held in infinite peace
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.72,1:17:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I was always sad
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.17,1:17:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,when it was over
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.17,1:17:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had to come
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.56,1:17:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,crashing back to earth
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.93,1:17:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.40,1:17:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that option to transcend the identification with the physicality
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.56,1:17:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and realize the truth that you're a spirit
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.18,1:17:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a great opportunity
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.67,1:17:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,man's catastrophe is
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.59,1:17:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,God's opportunity is the favorite saying about that isn't it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.31,1:17:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.14,1:17:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,by contemplation
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.47,1:17:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and meditation is a different thing
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.47,1:17:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but by contemplation
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.47,1:17:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of identifying with form
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.47,1:17:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,with content
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.47,1:17:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionalizing it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.47,1:17:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,getting positionalized about it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.47,1:17:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and reactive to it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.47,1:17:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you become non-attached
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.47,1:17:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you become the observer witness
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.47,1:18:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a contemplative lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.10,1:18:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah you know what's going on
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.10,1:18:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I got the gist of it all
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.10,1:18:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,how many videos do I have to see of disaster
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.10,1:18:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean I got it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.10,1:18:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.14,1:18:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,total disaster in all of its expression
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.14,1:18:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,all of its expressions
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.14,1:18:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you get it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.14,1:18:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,without getting caught in it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.52,1:18:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,oh it's so sad
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.52,1:18:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,oh it's so bad
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.52,1:18:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to emotionalize about it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.52,1:18:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because emotionalizing doesn't help anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.52,1:18:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,see
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.52,1:18:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of a crisis
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.52,1:18:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need people that are blubbering and crying
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.52,1:18:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you need a cool head
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.61,1:18:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're on the verge of death
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.61,1:18:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to be cool
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.39,1:18:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you're about to blow up
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.42,1:18:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you're second from disaster
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.42,1:18:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,second from disaster
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.44,1:18:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you just become very calm
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.44,1:18:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,alright
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.44,1:18:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,super calm
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.56,1:18:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and then
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.56,1:18:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionalize about it later
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.81,1:18:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,on TV or on a blog site
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.81,1:18:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.92,1:19:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.92,1:19:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,okay
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.72,1:19:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so you
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.72,1:19:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a contemplative lifestyle then
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.72,1:19:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is an awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.72,1:19:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you open yourself to be
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.72,1:19:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,aware of the field
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.72,1:19:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than the content of the field
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.72,1:19:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the field tells you whether it's safe or not safe
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.44,1:19:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the field tells you what the overall intention is
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.44,1:19:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's closer to intention
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.44,1:19:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and non-verbal non-linear knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.77,1:19:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,like a knowingness comes forth
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.77,1:19:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,yes there is such a thing as population karma
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.77,1:19:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,then you can go and verify it
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.77,1:19:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you see
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.77,1:19:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it just seemed like an awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.77,1:19:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but it doesn't come out of thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.77,1:19:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it just comes out of being with
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.77,1:19:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the overall situation
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.77,1:19:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,being with the overall situation
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.72,1:19:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we all send help in whatever linear form we can
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.72,1:19:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we all send checks and do what we can
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.72,1:19:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in the linear domain
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.85,1:19:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but to the person who's laying there in the foxhole
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.85,1:19:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,linear domain is
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.85,1:20:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,not all that interesting at the moment
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.85,1:20:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because what's up
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.85,1:20:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're up against is spirit
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.85,1:20:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you're up against whether
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.85,1:20:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.21,1:20:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,feel
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.21,1:20:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,safe no matter what
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.21,1:20:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,bodies come and bodies go
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.78,1:20:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,your attitude is going to be the result of the context
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.78,1:20:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so when we pray for people as we did
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.78,1:20:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we're trying to send spiritual energy to the context
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.78,1:20:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so that somebody who is about ready to give up
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.78,1:20:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and hopeless
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.78,1:20:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly feels
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.78,1:20:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,no I'll keep going
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.78,1:20:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,where did they get the oh I'll keep going
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.78,1:20:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,they got it from being the upliftment
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.78,1:20:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because as we hold them in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.78,1:20:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and do om or pray
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.78,1:20:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we uplift the field
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.78,1:20:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby everybody's upliftment
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.78,1:20:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is uplifted in the field
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.14,1:20:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind evolves by the upliftment of the field
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.14,1:20:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,upliftment of the field
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.80,1:21:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so we withdraw then to the watcher
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.80,1:21:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.80,1:21:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.80,1:21:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and once
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.80,1:21:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you get in the habit of being the witness of the phenomena
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.93,1:21:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,then over time
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.93,1:21:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,even the witness disappears
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.93,1:21:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for a time there is identifying with the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.93,1:21:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but pretty soon you realize the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.93,1:21:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,disappears
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.93,1:21:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and that comes about because witnessing is happening of its own
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.06,1:21:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no you that is doing the witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.06,1:21:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no this or that
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.06,1:21:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the witnessing is happening of its own
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.06,1:21:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,there isn't any you doing a witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.14,1:21:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so that gets you out of the duality of a separate me
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.14,1:21:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and of that
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.47,1:21:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the witnessing is happening of its own
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.07,1:21:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it always is
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.43,1:21:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the other way the last lecture was supposed to be on
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.52,1:21:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,equanimity or something wasn't it
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.52,1:21:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,yes
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.43,1:21:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we forgot to mention it anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.43,1:22:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so equanimity then comes from non-attachment
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.19,1:22:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,detachment
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.19,1:22:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you become the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.19,1:22:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and being the witness you have no positionality about
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.19,1:22:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what is going on
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.19,1:22:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you have no positionality
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.28,1:22:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so you are detached
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.28,1:22:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and pretty soon the observer witness goes away
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.52,1:22:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and what is
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.60,1:22:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the only thing left is consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.93,1:22:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.09,1:22:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,without a subject and an object
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.09,1:22:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a non-dualistic way of being
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.76,1:22:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore contemplative lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.76,1:22:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,eventuates
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.34,1:22:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,into a non-linear non-dualistic way of being
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.34,1:22:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,way of being
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.47,1:22:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and your way of being then
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.47,1:22:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is in a greater accord with reality than it is with content
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.68,1:22:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're the witness you get the total same
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.68,1:23:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to hear somebody blubbering
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.19,1:23:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we need help here
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.19,1:23:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,right
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.44,1:23:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,ten thousand people in disaster
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.27,1:23:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like saying isn't that a beautiful sunset
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.27,1:23:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you know the way to kill a sunset is
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.27,1:23:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody is getting off on a sunset
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.27,1:23:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and somebody says isn't that a beautiful sunset
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.27,1:23:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,unnecessary protrusion
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.27,1:23:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,or isn't that beautiful music
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.27,1:23:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it was so you spoke yes
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.26,1:23:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the contemplative person gets it
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.26,1:23:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,when we were in Europe you know
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.60,1:23:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrating the Greek cathedrals
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.60,1:23:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it was really astonishing
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.60,1:23:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd walk into this incredible cathedral
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.60,1:23:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible sculpture
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.60,1:23:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see even one cornice
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.60,1:23:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it took a man's entire lifetime to dedicate
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.60,1:23:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because all the workmen are dedicating their efforts to God
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.60,1:24:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,here's this incredible
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.71,1:24:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been there a thousand years
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.22,1:24:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in England the one I first spoke at in 71
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.43,1:24:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been there a thousand years
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.43,1:24:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't think of the name of it at the moment
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.43,1:24:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,oh yeah right yes
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.43,1:24:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.27,1:24:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so here you are in these incredible cathedrals
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.27,1:24:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and people are running around with their cell phones
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.27,1:24:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,talking to their mother
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.27,1:24:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,ordering merchandise
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.27,1:24:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it's like studying you see
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.27,1:24:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.27,1:24:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sort of annoyed
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.31,1:24:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that happened also in France
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.36,1:24:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in Chartres I think it was yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.63,1:24:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought you know
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.63,1:24:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,where are the people running this cathedral you know
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.63,1:24:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean I would be telling them
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.63,1:24:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,shush or get out
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.63,1:24:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.63,1:24:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah but I guess this is the era of self-expression
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.68,1:24:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.88,1:24:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,self-expression
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.88,1:24:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,talking on your cell phone
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.88,1:25:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.88,1:25:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,unbelievable right
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.88,1:25:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like missing the entire context
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.88,1:25:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so caught up in this personal
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.88,1:25:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,self-interest content
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.92,1:25:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that they don't even get
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.92,1:25:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what it's about
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.92,1:25:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,same thing happened in the Lincoln Memorial in Washington DC
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.92,1:25:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it always makes you speechless
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.92,1:25:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.92,1:25:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not like a picture of it
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.92,1:25:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of it is just stunning overwhelming
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.92,1:25:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity you're just confronted with
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.19,1:25:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity do or die kind of integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.52,1:25:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is there
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.52,1:25:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,grandeur the grandeur of integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.52,1:25:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.52,1:25:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and there again people were you know
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.77,1:25:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,on their cell phones
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.77,1:25:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so we're gonna take a break
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.15,1:25:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,did you enjoy the little brief thing with kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.15,1:25:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know I thought it's
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.15,1:25:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we've never done it you know
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.64,1:26:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're not teaching kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.64,1:26:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm not trying to convince anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.64,1:26:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have no vested interest
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.64,1:26:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in owning any kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.64,1:26:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,things you know
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.64,1:26:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you want to ignore it
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.92,1:26:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth is exactly the same
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.92,1:26:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,without the calibrations
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.92,1:26:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth is exactly the same
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.14,1:26:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the calibration does
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.14,1:26:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is give you a verification from the linear domain
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.14,1:26:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you can remain a modern human
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.14,1:26:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.14,1:26:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,who's used to logic and proof and all that kind of thing
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.14,1:26:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and move with comfort and ease into the non
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.14,1:26:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,linear non-provable
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.14,1:26:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,subjective experiential
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.14,1:26:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.06,1:26:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so we'll meet again after
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.06,1:26:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,11.30
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.31,1:26:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,11.30
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.31,1:27:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,okay
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.64,1:27:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we were talking about serenity
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.64,1:27:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,equanimity
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.38,1:27:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in the last lecture
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.38,1:27:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.38,1:27:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,there was
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.38,1:27:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,one important thing I
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.23,1:27:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,forgot although I've spoken of it many times
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.50,1:27:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in the contemplative state also it facilitates
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.68,1:27:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,being with the silent space
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.68,1:27:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which thinkingness arises
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.68,1:27:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,now
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.68,1:27:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,this can be discovered
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.23,1:27:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.23,1:27:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it also occurs of its own
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.23,1:27:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,via contemplation
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.27,1:27:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.21,1:27:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,presumes that thoughts are linear
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.48,1:27:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.48,1:27:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's being caused by this that or the other thing
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.48,1:28:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and it goes off into
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.15,1:28:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,never never land
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.15,1:28:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,once the mind starts thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.15,1:28:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it's unstoppable
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.15,1:28:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore to try and look
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.43,1:28:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't find
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.43,1:28:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a peace between two thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.43,1:28:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've said this before
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.43,1:28:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the mistranslations of the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.92,1:28:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with that
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.92,1:28:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite space is not between two thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.14,1:28:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite space is prior to thought
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.14,1:28:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,okay let's see if that's correct
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.76,1:28:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the statement
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.76,1:28:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,if we have permission
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.76,1:28:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is correct oh lord
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.76,1:28:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,yes
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.76,1:28:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.76,1:28:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as far as we can see
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.76,1:28:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,experientially you'll notice
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.76,1:28:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,if you watch thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.10,1:28:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,they start out as sort of a vague urge
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.10,1:28:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,like dogginess arises
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.39,1:28:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it becomes dog
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.39,1:28:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,then it becomes rover
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.39,1:28:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it goes into how rover was run over
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.39,1:29:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and then how we all cried
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.39,1:29:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you know it's a whole long story
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.96,1:29:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in meditation with one pointedness of mind
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.09,1:29:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you witness the emergence of thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.11,1:29:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and you surrender them
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.27,1:29:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,at their point of origination
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.27,1:29:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,now in the beginning
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.27,1:29:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you decide that you can let go
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.27,1:29:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the sad story of how rover got run over
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.27,1:29:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and how the children cried
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.27,1:29:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that crap
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.27,1:29:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you can let all that emotion out of you
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.27,1:29:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we know it was tragic
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.31,1:29:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,okay
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.88,1:29:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you've already thought that sad tragic thought
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.88,1:29:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,probably four or five hundred times
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.88,1:29:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not exactly news
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.61,1:29:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,okay
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.61,1:29:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll notice
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.19,1:29:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that one is enamored of thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.19,1:29:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that the experience or edge of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.56,1:29:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,survives on thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.56,1:29:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it gets desperate
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.56,1:29:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,when there's nothing going on
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.56,1:30:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and it resorts to thinkingness to stay alive
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.15,1:30:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because the ego has no source of energy
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.15,1:30:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,other than animal energy
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.15,1:30:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't have spiritual energy
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.39,1:30:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual energy doesn't arrive
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.39,1:30:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,till consciousness level 200
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.73,1:30:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so it seeks
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.22,1:30:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,some kind of gain
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.22,1:30:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience or edge of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.22,1:30:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is always out there
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.22,1:30:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,milking everything
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.22,1:30:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for what kind of juice it can get out of
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.22,1:30:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,tragedy
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.22,1:30:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,oh poor old rover
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.22,1:30:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,oh
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.22,1:30:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,oh the worst of the story
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.18,1:30:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,before the ego thrives
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.18,1:30:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,oh my god
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.18,1:30:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it was the ultimate tragedy
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.18,1:30:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and the steers start
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.39,1:30:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that's how the ego feeds itself
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.39,1:30:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it juices it
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.39,1:30:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't want to let it go
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.39,1:30:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the obstacle
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.39,1:30:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is the
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.39,1:30:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,ego is getting such juice
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.39,1:30:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,out of negativity
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.39,1:30:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that it clings to it
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.39,1:31:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the egotistic display
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.43,1:31:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you gotta get on the blog site
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.51,1:31:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell the world what you think about it
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.07,1:31:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the world's been waiting for it
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.07,1:31:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,all these centuries
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.27,1:31:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's funny
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.27,1:31:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.27,1:31:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,alright
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.64,1:31:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so you're willing to give up the self indulgence
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.64,1:31:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of thinking this
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.64,1:31:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and the juice that you're getting out of all the drama
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.88,1:31:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.88,1:31:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you're getting juice out of the fear of the future
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.88,1:31:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you're getting juice out of clinging and grief out of the past
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.88,1:31:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,those are the obstacles
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.97,1:31:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the primary obstacle
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.97,1:31:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is the juice that you're getting out of the experience or edge
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.97,1:31:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,alright
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.97,1:31:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you walk away from it
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.44,1:31:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is you have to surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.44,1:31:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to first see
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.44,1:31:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that all the ego's positionalities
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.44,1:31:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,are devices to
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.44,1:31:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,juice energy out of them
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.44,1:31:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,out of being right
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.44,1:31:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,getting even
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.44,1:31:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,being richer
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.44,1:32:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,more famous
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.44,1:32:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,more
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.44,1:32:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,being right
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.44,1:32:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,getting even
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.44,1:32:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,holding a grudge
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.69,1:32:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,people will hold a grudge an entire lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.21,1:32:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,entire lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.21,1:32:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the diet aids
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.21,1:32:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.21,1:32:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the same grudge they've had all these years
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.27,1:32:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,oh god
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.27,1:32:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.65,1:32:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah I remember that
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.46,1:32:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah I remember that
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.46,1:32:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,after the world war two
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.46,1:32:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you know after the war was over
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.97,1:32:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,almost instantly both sides forgave each other
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.97,1:32:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,almost instantly
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.68,1:32:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,freaking war is over
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.68,1:32:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.68,1:32:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so you salute the kamikaze pilots
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.68,1:32:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean they did what they could for their country
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.68,1:32:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with their white thing going
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.68,1:32:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and their bravery
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.68,1:32:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and their courage
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.68,1:32:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and both sides respect each other
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.68,1:32:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is fine
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.68,1:32:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,they even celebrate together
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.85,1:32:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,some members of the opposite sides became lifetime friends
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.85,1:32:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote books about it
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.85,1:33:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and some people hung on to it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.10,1:33:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw a veteran on TV not long ago
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.10,1:33:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.10,1:33:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.35,1:33:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,50 years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.35,1:33:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's still hanging on to it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.35,1:33:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,he still hates them
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.35,1:33:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,50 years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.55,1:33:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we were all forgiving each other
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.55,1:33:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody was doing what they had to do at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.55,1:33:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for god
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.80,1:33:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for country
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.80,1:33:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Fuhrer
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.80,1:33:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever you thought you were supposed to do
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.80,1:33:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.80,1:33:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan and the Hirohito was
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.80,1:33:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the sun god
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.80,1:33:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,descendant of the sun god
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.80,1:33:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so you did it for god
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.80,1:33:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so each one does what he sees as the good
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.86,1:33:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,now the experiencer
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.14,1:33:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is the advancing edge of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.14,1:33:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is the processor
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.32,1:33:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencer processes everything
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.46,1:33:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it processes it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.46,1:33:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,one ten thousandths of a second
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.22,1:33:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,after the event
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.64,1:33:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.64,1:33:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you never experience anything
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.64,1:34:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you experience the ego itself
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.80,1:34:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a readout of it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.40,1:34:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,if you have permission to ask this oh lord
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.82,1:34:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,what I just spoke was the absolute truth
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.82,1:34:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute truth oh lord
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.69,1:34:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,amen
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.69,1:34:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,resist
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.69,1:34:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the absolute truth as far as we can verify
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.69,1:34:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see what I did with kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.69,1:34:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to verify it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.69,1:34:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's a new thought
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.85,1:34:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,never even heard of it expressed before
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.85,1:34:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never heard it expressed before
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.02,1:34:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.61,1:34:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,this experiencer is out there
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.81,1:34:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to juice things
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.81,1:34:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.81,1:34:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so what's coming out of this
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.80,1:34:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is then the readout
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.80,1:34:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so what you think is experiencing out there-ness
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.89,1:34:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is not out there-ness
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.89,1:34:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the ego's readout of out there-ness
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.89,1:35:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it is so fast
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.31,1:35:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,one ten thousandths of a second
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.31,1:35:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that you cannot catch it
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.31,1:35:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason you can't
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.85,1:35:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,glimpse an infinite space between two thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.19,1:35:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is that which the perceiver
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.72,1:35:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is moving at the same rate as the thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.72,1:35:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you see
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.72,1:35:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have to move faster than one ten thousandths of a second to catch it
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.72,1:35:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,well the mind can't move faster
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.47,1:35:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,move that fast
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.47,1:35:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,so to use the mind to try and find an empty space
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.47,1:35:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,between two thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.47,1:35:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't work
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.27,1:35:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know of anybody who became enlightened
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.27,1:35:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,by noting the space between two thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.27,1:35:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,by certain meditative techniques
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.17,1:35:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you can hit a momentary saturity
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.17,1:35:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but it doesn't last
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.17,1:35:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and when you get up and open your eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.17,1:35:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencer takes hold again
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.17,1:36:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in the enlightened state then
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.64,1:36:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,at a certain level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.64,1:36:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens is the experiencer dissolves
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.64,1:36:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and then
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.64,1:36:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the brilliance and radiance
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.93,1:36:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of divinity as all of existence shines forth
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.02,1:36:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and stuns the mind silent
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.22,1:36:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it's possible then to let go of the
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.82,1:36:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,desire to think earlier and earlier in the game
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.82,1:36:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you feel the dogginess coming up
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.07,1:36:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and you surrender it as it arises
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.07,1:36:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you follow the emergence of the thought
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.07,1:36:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually you come to the realization
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.18,1:36:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's an energy of thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.18,1:36:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an energy that's creating this endless stream of thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.52,1:37:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and beneath that
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.92,1:37:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,if you surrender that
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.92,1:37:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is infinite silence
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.92,1:37:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,ninety-nine percent of the mind is silent
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.00,1:37:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to find the silence space
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.86,1:37:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is not between thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.86,1:37:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but a priori
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.86,1:37:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's like the sea
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.06,1:37:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've given the analogy of the flying fish coming out of the sea
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.06,1:37:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a still sea
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.25,1:37:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which the thoughts are arising individually
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.25,1:37:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not very difficult
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.10,1:37:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact you can even do it while I'm talking
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.10,1:37:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm going to do the same thing
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.27,1:37:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,beneath the field of thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.72,1:37:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there is infinite silence
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.72,1:37:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the infinite silence
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.72,1:37:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear the doc talking about what he's talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.72,1:37:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no relationship to him
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.72,1:37:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not interested in him
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.72,1:37:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,frankly I don't even care what he's talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.72,1:38:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite silence space is
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.53,1:38:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is the next step from contemplation
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.34,1:38:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,see with contemplation you're not wanting to do anything
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.34,1:38:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to what's happening out there
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.34,1:38:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to rescue this person
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.34,1:38:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to challenge him
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.34,1:38:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to challenge this person
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.34,1:38:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to thump this person's chest
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.34,1:38:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is just being what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.50,1:38:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,being what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.72,1:38:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what does the thing mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.72,1:38:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you exactly what everything means
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.72,1:38:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what it means is what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.72,1:38:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,what it means is what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.61,1:38:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,identity is its meaning
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.61,1:38:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that saves you all kinds of cerebration
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.35,1:38:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,what does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.35,1:38:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it means what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.39,1:38:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you the analogy of the cat
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.82,1:38:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you ask the cat
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.82,1:38:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you're telling a cat about being a cat
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.94,1:39:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and the cat says what does cat mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.94,1:39:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you get down to the encyclopedia and the dictionary
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.10,1:39:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and you read them all what it says about cat
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.10,1:39:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the cat says that's got nothing to do with me
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.26,1:39:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that's your head talking
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.76,1:39:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what's that got to do with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.76,1:39:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say to the cat
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.56,1:39:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,well then who are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.78,1:39:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the cat says I'm me
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.81,1:39:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm me that's what the cat is
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.81,1:39:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the reality is subjectivity
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.03,1:39:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the cat doesn't know anything about catness
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.03,1:39:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that's all
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.03,1:39:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,mentalization
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.03,1:39:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so the only reality is that of existence
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.64,1:39:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of being that
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.64,1:39:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore the enlightened state is merely to surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.64,1:39:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that is not the self with a capital S
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.64,1:40:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and one automatically is left with what one is
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.15,1:40:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so enlightenment is not the attainment of something new
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.35,1:40:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the relinquishment of everything that stands in the way
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.35,1:40:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the surrender of everything
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.35,1:40:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so to understand the mechanisms of the ego and how it works
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.35,1:40:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,puts you at a tremendous advantage
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.35,1:40:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to undo every negative thing you could ever think about
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.40,1:40:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or every experience you've ever had etc
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.40,1:40:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to merely witness
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.89,1:40:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so from the contemplative style
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.89,1:40:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you become the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.89,1:40:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you become the witness of how the experience is
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.89,1:40:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you experience your edge
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.89,1:40:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is out there trying to juice things
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.89,1:40:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and a true renunciate
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.89,1:40:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,then renounces that payoff of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.89,1:40:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,denies it reality
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.21,1:40:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to wear sackcloth and ashes
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.21,1:40:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to live on figs and nuts
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.21,1:40:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and other disgusting diets
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.21,1:40:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to wear sandals
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.76,1:40:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to shave your head
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.77,1:40:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and retreat to a cave
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.77,1:41:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,not necessary
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.81,1:41:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you do it by intention now
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.47,1:41:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,just let go of the whole audience
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.47,1:41:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't care less what the audience thinks, feels
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.47,1:41:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,whether they learned anything
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.68,1:41:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm completely and totally indifferent to it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.68,1:41:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't care less
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.52,1:41:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that took one instant
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.44,1:41:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,see, I didn't have to undress, wear sandals
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.44,1:41:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,go someplace
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.44,1:41:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and eat weird things for 30 years
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.44,1:41:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that's an inner decision
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.18,1:41:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to let go of the payoff
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.18,1:41:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the satisfaction, oh the audience is pleased
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.18,1:41:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or the fear the audience is not pleased
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.18,1:41:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or gee I might be boring them
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.18,1:41:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or oh oh I might be repeating myself
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.18,1:41:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,or you know what I'm saying
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.53,1:41:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that would screw up your head totally
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.53,1:41:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,what are you even talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.53,1:41:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it's got my head screwed up
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.53,1:41:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,golly I wonder if they are happy
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.85,1:41:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with what I'm talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.31,1:41:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,oh poor old rover
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.31,1:41:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember how he got run over
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.52,1:42:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,poor old rover
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.52,1:42:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I gotta quit juicing fear
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.00,1:42:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,okay
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.00,1:42:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,could you let go and please everybody
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.00,1:42:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,yep
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.00,1:42:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how long would it take you?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.00,1:42:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,done
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.22,1:42:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so the easiest way into it
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.43,1:42:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is a contemplative lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.23,1:42:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you are only being that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.30,1:42:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing is required
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.39,1:42:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no this or that
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.39,1:42:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,everything happens spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.61,1:42:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and as you retreat from the juice
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.03,1:42:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of thinking this then
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.03,1:42:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you let go wanting to think
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.44,1:42:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,could you surrender wanting to think
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.44,1:42:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,would you be willing to surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.44,1:42:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,your thinkingness to God?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.44,1:42:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I surrender this thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.71,1:42:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to thee oh Lord
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.71,1:42:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,uh huh
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.18,1:42:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and you step back into the silence
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.18,1:42:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and you live in the silence
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.18,1:42:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the noise goes on
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.69,1:43:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the world goes on
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.69,1:43:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the bombs go off
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.69,1:43:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the buses collide
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.69,1:43:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's all out there
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.18,1:43:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's what Ramana Maharshi means
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.97,1:43:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the world you think you see
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.35,1:43:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't even exist yet
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.35,1:43:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that's true if you're at consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.38,1:43:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,at 720
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.38,1:43:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're not I wouldn't walk across the street
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.38,1:43:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,with your eyes closed
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.51,1:43:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,one thing about spiritual truth is
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.51,1:43:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to be
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.51,1:43:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.51,1:43:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to the level that you're at
Dialogue: 0,1:43:37.51,1:43:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it sounds good
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.56,1:43:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you know that the world you see is
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.72,1:43:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's at 720 or so
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.72,1:43:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,see
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.72,1:43:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that's true
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.76,1:43:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that's true if you're at 720
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.76,1:43:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not true if the sheriff is
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.76,1:43:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at your door
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.28,1:44:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so the way to serenity then
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.72,1:44:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is to
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.98,1:44:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,witness
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.98,1:44:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,by witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.98,1:44:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you get that the experiencer is out there
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.98,1:44:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,juicing everything
Dialogue: 0,1:44:12.98,1:44:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,now we saw how the ego arose
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.98,1:44:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,over great periods of time
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.98,1:44:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw that
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.11,1:44:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,four and a half billion years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.34,1:44:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever the great bang
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.34,1:44:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,please don't send me an email
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.34,1:44:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it wasn't four and a half billion years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.34,1:44:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,a long long time ago
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.34,1:44:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,my understanding which I
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.82,1:44:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't give credit to history channel
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.82,1:44:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,where did all my
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.82,1:44:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that's all my education of history
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.82,1:44:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.82,1:44:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,as a child I slept through history
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.82,1:44:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it was so boring
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.82,1:44:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because you just had to memorize dates
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.82,1:44:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and now history is so vital and interesting
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.82,1:44:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to stay up late and watch the history channel
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.82,1:44:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,all the stuff I miss
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.82,1:44:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is the grade school
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.82,1:44:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it's very exciting and dramatic
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.82,1:44:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and I love it
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.05,1:44:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway so
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.11,1:45:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of our planet Earth
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.11,1:45:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and our planetary system then
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.11,1:45:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,this spinning lava
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.11,1:45:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,spun through space
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.11,1:45:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.11,1:45:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,slowly cooled off
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.11,1:45:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,a crust formed
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.21,1:45:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and then
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.21,1:45:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the interface of
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.21,1:45:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the light of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.21,1:45:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness as the light of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.21,1:45:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,interacting with matter
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.21,1:45:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,when local conditions permit
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.21,1:45:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,emerges as life
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.43,1:45:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so all life is of divine origin
Dialogue: 0,1:45:30.56,1:45:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the physical mechanical world
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.56,1:45:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is of a different order of existence
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.56,1:45:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,this order cannot create
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.56,1:45:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,this order
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.56,1:45:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,those of you that understand abstract intellectual
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.56,1:45:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,dialectic
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.88,1:45:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot jump level
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.23,1:45:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,this level cannot cause this level
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.23,1:45:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.84,1:45:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.84,1:45:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,interacting with matter
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.84,1:45:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so matter interacting with matter
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.22,1:46:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is incapable of creating life
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.22,1:46:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a true statement of the Lord
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.67,1:46:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,resist
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.98,1:46:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,matter interacting with matter
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.98,1:46:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is incapable of producing life
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.98,1:46:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because life is of a completely different order
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.98,1:46:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,high level of
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.98,1:46:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,abstraction
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.98,1:46:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a completely different paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.98,1:46:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with different qualities
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.98,1:46:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy required
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.48,1:46:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to create life is infinite
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.48,1:46:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which is great
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.64,1:46:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that's much greater than all the universes
Dialogue: 0,1:46:32.64,1:46:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,put together
Dialogue: 0,1:46:33.64,1:46:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,clanking together
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.64,1:46:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is still not infinite
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.64,1:46:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,no it takes the energy
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.64,1:46:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,an infinite omnipotence
Dialogue: 0,1:46:41.64,1:46:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which arises life
Dialogue: 0,1:46:43.64,1:46:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and its interaction with matter
Dialogue: 0,1:46:45.64,1:46:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,when divinity looks at matter
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.64,1:46:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,matters lit up
Dialogue: 0,1:46:49.64,1:46:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,emerges as a new paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:46:51.88,1:46:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,okay
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.88,1:46:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so life then emerges as creation
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.11,1:46:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that's good to know
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.11,1:47:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because if life is an aspect of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.11,1:47:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,then it can't be extinguished
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.11,1:47:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be extinguished
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.11,1:47:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so we have another addition to man's knowledge
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.11,1:47:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we have the survival of matter
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.61,1:47:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and energy
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.61,1:47:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and now we have
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.61,1:47:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the indestructibility of life itself
Dialogue: 0,1:47:20.61,1:47:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,thus we're reaffirmed just again
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.61,1:47:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we're not using kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:47:24.88,1:47:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,except to just affirm the reality of what is obvious
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.88,1:47:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what's obvious
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.88,1:47:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,okay
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.88,1:47:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what's obvious is that life is indistinguishable
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.88,1:47:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and that death is not a possibility
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.88,1:47:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,resist
Dialogue: 0,1:47:36.88,1:47:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,yes
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.88,1:47:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for death to be a possibility
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.88,1:47:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,God would have to be subject to mortality
Dialogue: 0,1:47:43.55,1:47:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand that?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.55,1:47:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:47:45.55,1:47:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,okay
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.39,1:47:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see electricity
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.39,1:47:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is independent of this toaster
Dialogue: 0,1:47:53.39,1:47:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and this cooking machine
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.39,1:47:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and this egg beater
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.39,1:47:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and this washing machine
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.39,1:47:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,now each
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.92,1:48:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the washing machine thinks it's the source of life
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.92,1:48:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,electricity
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.92,1:48:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so does the toaster
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.92,1:48:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the washing machine says
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.92,1:48:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the source of electricity
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.92,1:48:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,now you're the locus
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.48,1:48:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you see
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.48,1:48:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so the source of life is like the electricity
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.48,1:48:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're plugged into it
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.48,1:48:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but you cannot extinguish electricity
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.48,1:48:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so life is not linear
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.48,1:48:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore it cannot go on and off
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.48,1:48:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,on-ness and off-ness
Dialogue: 0,1:48:25.64,1:48:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is only a consequence of linearity
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.64,1:48:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is non-linear
Dialogue: 0,1:48:29.64,1:48:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,has no beginning and no ending
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.64,1:48:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore no origination
Dialogue: 0,1:48:31.64,1:48:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore no finality
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.64,1:48:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore death is not a possibility
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.64,1:48:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,law of the conservation of life
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.64,1:48:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why man never discovered that
Dialogue: 0,1:48:40.64,1:48:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,he's got
Dialogue: 0,1:48:41.64,1:48:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,law of conservation of energy
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.64,1:48:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of matter
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.64,1:48:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you say
Dialogue: 0,1:48:45.64,1:48:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.64,1:48:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.64,1:48:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.64,1:48:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and life idiot
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.64,1:48:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,can't see the most obvious
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.28,1:48:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah it's because it's right before you
Dialogue: 0,1:48:57.28,1:48:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't see the most obvious
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.28,1:49:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so then
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.96,1:49:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a contemplative lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,1:49:03.96,1:49:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is progressively non-linear
Dialogue: 0,1:49:05.96,1:49:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:49:07.56,1:49:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the witnesser
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.56,1:49:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you will quickly
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.56,1:49:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,gather
Dialogue: 0,1:49:12.56,1:49:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is doing it on its own
Dialogue: 0,1:49:16.10,1:49:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not a you witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:49:18.27,1:49:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just witnessing witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:49:20.27,1:49:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's autonomous
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.27,1:49:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,witnessing is autonomous
Dialogue: 0,1:49:24.27,1:49:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an aspect of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.27,1:49:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't need a personal you
Dialogue: 0,1:49:28.27,1:49:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it only needs a personal you to report it
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.27,1:49:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as a person
Dialogue: 0,1:49:32.46,1:49:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,subjective experience to report it
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.18,1:49:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the witnessing then becomes more abstract
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.18,1:49:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and moves into consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.18,1:49:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the realization that consciousness is also beyond volition
Dialogue: 0,1:49:48.22,1:49:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness is autonomous happening of its own
Dialogue: 0,1:49:52.22,1:49:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it is what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:49:54.31,1:49:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,complete and total
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.40,1:49:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so the realization then eventually comes
Dialogue: 0,1:49:59.40,1:50:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and it opens up into realization
Dialogue: 0,1:50:02.40,1:50:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presence of the self as
Dialogue: 0,1:50:05.40,1:50:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the inner author of one's own existence
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.34,1:50:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the source of one's joy
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.34,1:50:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.34,1:50:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,pleasure and joy does not come from out there
Dialogue: 0,1:50:14.34,1:50:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,accomplishment
Dialogue: 0,1:50:15.34,1:50:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,possessions
Dialogue: 0,1:50:16.34,1:50:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,vanity
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.34,1:50:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,things like that
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.60,1:50:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it comes from the subjective exquisite completeness
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.60,1:50:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that in and of myself
Dialogue: 0,1:50:24.60,1:50:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I am complete and total and need nothing
Dialogue: 0,1:50:28.97,1:50:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in and of myself oh lord
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.97,1:50:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I am complete and total and need nothing
Dialogue: 0,1:50:36.97,1:50:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a statement of the absolute truth
Dialogue: 0,1:50:38.97,1:50:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,resist
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.48,1:50:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,yes
Dialogue: 0,1:50:41.48,1:50:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so the more evolved you become
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.48,1:50:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the less you need
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.48,1:50:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't really need anything
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.72,1:50:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,they're conveniences
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.72,1:50:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,they're conveniences
Dialogue: 0,1:50:47.72,1:50:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you can do without money
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.81,1:50:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you can do without anything
Dialogue: 0,1:50:49.81,1:50:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.81,1:50:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,walked away from everything
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.81,1:50:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,sold truckloads of manure
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.81,1:50:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,great
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.81,1:50:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,ten bucks to fill it up
Dialogue: 0,1:50:55.19,1:50:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,sold it for forty
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.19,1:50:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what more do you need
Dialogue: 0,1:50:57.19,1:50:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a cot from the dime store
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.55,1:50:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I lived in that for years
Dialogue: 0,1:50:59.55,1:51:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple of blankets I got from the goodwill
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.55,1:51:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and a box next to the bed
